				<strong class="title">General Comment</strong>From what ive heard,this song is sung backwards, so from what i could piece to gether its just a little tale about a crumbling society thats about to go through great change through the actions of two men.<br />
<br />
The last verse describes the place with princes watching over the city and its servants, as two men come charging in the distance. The two previous verses as i see it are the conversation thats taking place as these two men ride to the palace/kings home in hope of a revolt or change of some kind.<br />
<br />
The Joker represents the honest working man who is always taken advantage of inspite of his hard work,"Businessmen, they drink my wine, plowmen dig my earth,<br />
None of them along the line know what any of it is worth."<br />
while the theif represents the man who has the chosen the dishonest but easier way of life. They have both come to an understanding over the patetic realities of life as the thief says " There are many here among us who feel that life is but a joke".<br />
As they approach the palace he says however that all the sad facts the joker is speaking of will not be there fate as they are going to confront their leader and hopefully bring about some kind of change.<br />
<br />
Thats pretty much all i could get.				
